Sample_Validation_Outlier_Detection

Joe McGirr

6/29/2020

For each plate, I labeled individuals from the same row on PC plots. If all individuals showed obviously wrong grouping, I labeled the row “bad”. “strange” indicates that one or two samples in the row showed odd grouping. (See PCA_row_labels.html to see all 160 plots that I checked to create the table).

Conclusion: Ploting by row in groups of 8 suggested obvious contamination in plates 1-5.

Not all rows of plates 1-5 showed contamination, but I removed all individuals from plate 1-5 to be conservative and reran PCA

Conclusion: TB shows clear structure, but all other populations overlap

PCA all individuals from plate 1-5 removed and TB removed

Conclusion: Little structure across populations other than TB

Double check patterns are consistent genome-wide with PLINK

Conclusion: Similar patterns genome-wide, with more separation of CA, and some strucutre within TB considering PC 4

plates 1-5 removed. 2017 samples. NGSAdmix

Conclusion: We might expect clearer grouping at k=6 based on geography, but we see a split within TB17 at k=5

Run PCA on each metapopulation separately to check for obvious outliers. Individuals from plates 1-5 removed
